MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Server (27/27 tests):
- BoardPin{author,text,sentAt,xPercent,yPercent} and BoardHighlight
  {author,quote,prefix,suffix,comment,sentAt} extend BoardItem
- ensureBoardItem: pinning/highlighting a page implicitly adds it to
  the board via canonicalKey — pin, highlight, and 'add to board' are
  the same underlying object, verified by test to not fork duplicates
- board_pin_add/remove, board_highlight_add/remove — membership-gated,
  removal restricted to admin or original author

Extension — the anchoring choices are the actual engineering here:
- lib/text-quote.ts: Text Quote Selector (Web Annotation pattern) —
  highlights are stored as the selected text + ~40 chars of surrounding
  context, re-found on load via string search rather than a DOM path
  or character offset, so they survive markup changes that would
  silently break a fragile anchor
- content script rewritten from passive-only into a full annotation
  overlay, injected via Shadow DOM (zero CSS bleed into host pages):
  - READ (every page load, zero network cost): matches the page's
    canonical key against communities already synced to local storage,
    renders pin markers (percent-positioned, scroll with the page) and
    highlights via the CSS Custom Highlight API (paints without
    mutating the page's DOM — can't break a React/Vue site's own
    rendering)
  - WRITE (only on actual pin/highlight submission): opens a short-
    lived, on-demand socket scoped to the tab, submits, caches the
    server's confirmation back to local storage so read-mode stays
    fresh even with the panel closed, disconnects after 4s idle —
    browsing normally never opens a connection
  - re-renders on SPA navigation (Airbnb/Amazon are client-routed)
  - Esc cancels either mode; click an existing pin to see/remove it

Panel: BoardView toolbar gains Pin and Highlight buttons (alongside
Add tab) that message the active tab's content script into that mode;
expanded item cards list pins and highlight quotes alongside comments.
